parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel pump assembly can cause fuel leaks, which can lead to fires or explosions, especially when in contact with hot engine components.
symptoms: fuel leaking from the fuel tank or pump cap
fuel dripping onto the engine or alternator

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the fuel level sensor can cause inaccurate fuel level readings, leading to unexpected fuel depletion or fuel starvation, which can cause the engine to stall or fail.
symptoms: fuel level gauge not functioning properly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to lock up, leading to a loss of control, increased stopping distance, and potentially resulting in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: the vehicle jerks or drops to one side
the stopping distance is significantly increased.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the transmission can cause the vehicle to shift out of gear, leading to loss of control, accidents, or leaving the driver stranded.
symptoms: The vehicle shifts out of gear
the transmission slips out of gear.
